sources.title: Porky's Five & Ten (1938)
sources.description: While Porky sails to the South Seas to open a store, thieving fish rob him of his cargo.

metadata.Plot: Porky sets sail for the Boola-Boola islands in the South Seas with a ship full of general merchandise and plans to open a 5 & 10 cent store. But a swordfish cuts a hole in the ship and Porky's goods fall into the ocean, where the fish make creative uses of them, ultimately opening a Hollywood nightclub, complete with fish impersonating various stars. Porky is saved when a waterspout comes along, re-stocking his ship.
metadata.Actors: Mel Blanc, Bill Days, Bernice Kamiat
